ble him to study the case file and assemble witnesses. The defendants pleaded not guilty to the charge. Their counsel, Mrs Iyanu Ayorinde, urged the court to grant the defendants bail, promising that they would not jump bail. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs Adefumike Anoma, granted the defendants bail in the sum of N20,000 with one surety each in like sum. Anoma adjourned the case until Jan.16 for further hearing. Vanguard An Ado-Ekiti Chief Magistrates’ Court, on Tuesday, ordered the remand of three men- Samuel Farotimi, Sunday Ajimoko and Tayo Ilugbo, for allegedly raping a 14-year-old girl. February 6, 2018 In "News" Four persons were yesterday arraigned before an Ado Ekiti Chief Magistrate Court for alleged attackedly attacking supporters of former of Ekiti State Gov. Mr. Ayo- dele Fayose, in Efon-Alaye on Nov. 20, 2012. December 4, 2012 In "News" Police on Thursday arraigned three persons at an Ire-Ekiti Magistrates’ Court, Ekiti state, for allegedly stealing a goat. November 17, 2016 In "News"